MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the ReportError stub with a Phase-2 placeholder emission for
CallBuiltinPointerInstruction. Mirrors CSAGenerator's shape but lowers
to a typed C++ function-pointer invoked through Builtins::CppEntryOf.

The BuiltinPtr value is a Tagged<Smi> carrying the Builtin enum id
(see PushBuiltinPointerInstruction), so we extract it with Smi::ToInt,
resolve via a static_cast<Builtin> to Builtins::CppEntryOf, reinterpret
the result as a FnPtr matching the BuiltinPointerType signature, and
call it with (isolate, args...).

Builtins::CppEntryOf does not exist yet — Phase 4 will generate a
builtins-cc-table.inc that provides it. Phase 2's correctness bar is
that the emission is syntactically valid C++ with the right signature
shape, which this patch satisfies.

Tail-calls to a BuiltinPtr are deferred (matches CSA's behaviour).
Multi-result return types remain unsupported (PairT deferral).
