Callee-side complement to CallCsaMacroAndBranchInstruction's caller-side
out-param rewrite (Task 3.5): when a labeled macro's body-CFG emits
'goto ExternalLabel(args...)', write each popped value into its T*
out-param, set the bool* label flag to true, and return from the macro
function.

Mirrors csa-generator.cc:846-853 structurally (reverse-iterate the
variable_names, pop and assign each), replacing ca_.Goto(<destination>)
with bool*-assignment + return. The <destination> string matches the
ExternalLabelName() form emitted when GenerateFunction eventually
produces standalone labeled-macro signatures under kCCBuiltins
(deferred — Phase 4 scope).

Phase 3 note: this emission is NOT exercised by any Phase 3 fixture.
kCCBuiltins does not yet emit standalone labeled-macro bodies (no
macro iteration pass for kCCBuiltins; GenerateFunction's label-exit
ReportError gate at implementation-visitor.cc:2056-2058 stays in
place for kCC/kCCDebug and has no kCCBuiltins arm). When a later
phase adds the macro-emission path, this code runs as-is without
modification.
